Description: Rim sherd of East Greek Wild Goat Style pottery dinos; interior reserved; exterior slipped white: on top of rim, guilloche with eyes, dots above and below; inside and outside of rim glazed; on body, reserved band above alternating red and black tongues.
Dimensions: Diameter: 25 - 33 centimetres (internal and external diameters of rim)
Curator's comments: Does not seem Chian, pace Lemos
Bibliographic references: Lemos 1991 / Archaic Pottery of Chios. The Decorated Styles (p. 246, no. 293)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GD.0006) (phase 2)
